A JOIN Clause is used to combines rows from two or more tables, based on related column between them

TYPES: 

(1) INNER JOIN : return record that have matching values in both tables

(2) LEFT JOIN : return all records from left table and the matched records from right table

(3) RIGHT JOIN : return all records from right table and matched records from left table

(4) FULL JOIN : returns all record when there is match in either left or right table